HEADWORD: on-line
<hw>on"-line`</hw></mhw> <pos>adj.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <fr>1</fr> <fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>connected by a
communications line to a computer. Opposite of
<ant>off-line</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> online, on line(predicate).</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <mark>[prenominal]</mark> <def>being in progress now;
ongoing; <as>as, <ex>on-line</ex> editorial projects</as>.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> ⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> in progress(predicate), ongoing, on
line(predicate).</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Onliness</ent>⟦br⟧
